00:45:19.254 --> 00:45:21.890
started off with, and I'm
curious how children answer it.

00:45:21.890 --> 00:45:24.280
Is there work-- to some
extent, whether or not

00:45:24.280 --> 00:45:26.640
this is a problem is dependent
on how the children who

00:45:26.640 --> 00:45:27.890
are reading these books react.

00:45:27.890 --> 00:45:28.420
PHILIP NEL: Right.

00:45:28.420 --> 00:45:29.878
AUDIENCE: Is there
work and studies

00:45:29.878 --> 00:45:32.620
you've done about whether
different races identify more

00:45:32.620 --> 00:45:35.530
or less strongly with the Cat
in the Hat, or is this something

00:45:35.530 --> 00:45:38.770
that really we're just looking
back and seeing and analyzing?

00:45:38.770 --> 00:45:39.520
PHILIP NEL: Yeah--

00:45:39.520 --> 00:45:40.570
AUDIENCE: Is that a
thing you can study,

00:45:40.570 --> 00:45:41.445
and have you done so?

00:45:41.445 --> 00:45:44.874
PHILIP NEL: No, I think
that's an excellent question.

00:45:44.874 --> 00:45:47.290
And as you know, the answer
"that's an excellent question"

00:45:47.290 --> 00:45:49.450
is the way of a speaker hedging.

00:45:49.450 --> 00:45:50.780
And so I'm hedging.

00:45:50.780 --> 00:45:53.230
And now I will offer
an imperfect answer

00:45:53.230 --> 00:45:55.450
to your excellent
question, which

00:45:55.450 --> 00:45:59.260
is that that's the central
question of a lot of children's

00:45:59.260 --> 00:46:00.460
literature scholarship.

00:46:00.460 --> 00:46:02.010
What do the children think?

00:46:02.010 --> 00:46:04.700
And it's tricky to answer
for a variety of reasons.

00:46:04.700 --> 00:46:06.040
First of all, you actually
have to do the research

00:46:06.040 --> 00:46:07.750
and go interview
individual children,

00:46:07.750 --> 00:46:09.850
because individual
children are all different

00:46:09.850 --> 00:46:11.814
and all respond
differently, and it's

00:46:11.814 --> 00:46:13.480
impossible to generalize
about children,

00:46:13.480 --> 00:46:15.970
as it is to generalize
about adults.

00:46:15.970 --> 00:46:18.640
And I have not done that
specific research on this.

00:46:18.640 --> 00:46:22.130
I have done the research
on the texts themselves,

00:46:22.130 --> 00:46:24.490
but I haven't done the
research on the children.

00:46:27.140 --> 00:46:28.600
Anecdotally, I can
tell you things,

00:46:28.600 --> 00:46:31.070
of people who, when I've talked
about the Cat in the Hat's

00:46:31.070 --> 00:46:33.680
minstrel ancestry,
have come up and said,

00:46:33.680 --> 00:46:36.580
gosh, he always
disturbed me, and I

00:46:36.580 --> 00:46:39.100
think I can now identify why.

00:46:39.100 --> 00:46:41.920
Even from when I was a child,
this character disturbed me.

00:46:41.920 --> 00:46:43.240
That's anecdotal.

00:46:43.240 --> 00:46:44.314
It's not quantitative.

00:46:44.314 --> 00:46:45.730
I don't think it
would pass muster

00:46:45.730 --> 00:46:49.000
for those of you working in
a major technology company,

00:46:49.000 --> 00:46:51.470
I'm just going to guess.

00:46:51.470 --> 00:46:54.545
But that's also part of the
reason for writing the book,

00:46:54.545 --> 00:46:56.920
is that there are a lot of
ways in which these things are

00:46:56.920 --> 00:46:58.450
hidden and unexplored.

00:46:58.450 --> 00:47:00.400
You could write 100
chapters on this.

00:47:00.400 --> 00:47:01.240
I just wrote five.

00:47:01.240 --> 00:47:03.790
But I think a sixth
chapter should

00:47:03.790 --> 00:47:10.666
be some kind of quantitative
study, which I did not do.

00:47:10.666 --> 00:47:12.040
There are other
studies you could

00:47:12.040 --> 00:47:14.500
cite, like on children's
responses to black dolls,

00:47:14.500 --> 00:47:15.070
for example.

00:47:15.070 --> 00:47:21.220
There are famous studies on
those, in which the children,

00:47:21.220 --> 00:47:24.120
even black children prefer the
white doll to the black doll,

00:47:24.120 --> 00:47:26.380
and those stories have
been cited as evidence

00:47:26.380 --> 00:47:29.442
that they learned racism.

00:47:29.442 --> 00:47:31.150
Another way to read
those is that they've

00:47:31.150 --> 00:47:33.766
